In this context, the Welsh letter W is pronounced in a similar way as the letter U is pronounced in the English Yorkshire dialect, more like an 'uh' sound.
Assembly Commission, which is currently developing laws to introduce the change of name, said: ‘Of course, it is the members themselves who have the last right of destination with regard to the name with which they are to be mentioned.’
